(9078, 338, 'artist_details_0_artist_bio', 'Melbourne-based Nicole Reed proclaims that, for her, photography is more than just a career – it’s her reason for living. Rarely leaving the house, never mind the country, without her camera, Nicole is proud to have been bitten by the travel bug and searches for the muse of her next frame around every corner. While her work is undoubtedly artistic, Nicole draws inspiration from magazines and documentary and reportage photography, favouring people as her subjects.\r\n\r\nNicole has exhibited in four solo shows, in Melbourne and Brisbane, and along with the publication T-world Journal has had a show on Cockatoo Island in Sydney as part of the 2012 Outpost Project which included 40 portraits printed at over 2 metres high. Nicole has also just recently had an exhibition of portraits at the National Gallery Of Victoria Studio which was included in the TEES project. Her work has appeared in a litany of publications, including T-world Journal, The Age Melbourne Magazine, Rolling Stone, The Herald Sun, J Mag, Tattoos Downunder, Inked Magazine, Beat, Desktop, Australian Creative, The Age newspaper, Artichoke, Inside, Wooden Toy, BeanScene,  Short Black, The Age Newspaper, Head Full of Snakes and Yen.\r\n\r\nNicole was the winner of The Desktop Create Award for Best Photographer in 2012 with her work for the New York Issue of T-world.'),
