(11572, 481, 'artist_details_0_artist_bio', 'From the fast paced world as news photographer, Nic Kocher, has developed into a public commentator and visual artist. He explores how new mediums influence the aesthetic of visual imagery and the multiple ways of telling stories through new technology that connects with viewers in a meaningful way.     Recently, Nic has employed the \'Cinemagraph\'. It is still image, where a small part of the frame moves, and usually loops. They explore the cyclical nature of time, how things repeat themselves over and over for eternity. They offer the quiet contemplation of the still image and give you time to look around the frame, examining the complexities of composition and subject matter, and at the same time offer a transition between one state and and the next.    “I want to explore how we relate to the spaces we live in, and I\'d like to tell the stories of some of the people who live there. The public and private areas that we habitat dictate how we interact and even how happy we are. I\'m interested in showing how we navigate these spaces and how we evolved with them. I like the idea of \'the outsider\' both as the artist\'s viewpoint and the subject matter.”'),
