(286, 3, '2013-11-27 12:33:41', '2013-11-27 12:33:41', '<i>Music, Melbourne &amp; Me: 40 years of Mushroom and Melbourne\'s Popular Music Culture </i>is a celebration of the last four decades of popular music represented through music, songs, posters, photographs, costumes, iconic rock venues and memorabilia from the private collection of Michael Gudinski AM, CEO of the Mushroom Group of Companies.\r\n\r\nRMIT Gallery opens all night for its last viewing of the extensive collection, and will feature a taster of mini 15 minute academic lectures on the subjects of celebrity, nostalgia and music.\r\n\r\nThe exhibition was developed from research by RMIT\'s Dr Kipps Horn, Program Director of the Music Industry program, and co-curated by RMIT Gallery Director and Chief Curator Suzanne Davies.', 'Melbourne, Music & Me: 40 years of Melbourne\'s Popular Music Culture', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'melbourne-music-me-40-years-of-melbournes-popular-music-culture', '', '', '2013-11-27 23:03:07', '2013-11-27 23:03:07', '', 0, 'http://whitenight.dev/?post_type=event&#038;p=286', 0, 'event', '', 0),
